Comment (src/views/admin/NotificationsView.vue:1021):
In `loadJobs()`, when a non-paginated request (no `cursor`) fails you clear `jobs.value`, but `jobsNextCursor` is left as-is. If a previous successful request set a cursor, the UI can incorrectly keep showing the “Load More” button even though the current result set is empty/errored. Consider setting `jobsNextCursor.value = null` when starting a fresh load and/or in the `catch` path for `!cursor` (and possibly when the latest request fails) so pagination state can’t become stale.
